'''Roy Smith''' (born 19 March 1936)<ref name="whustats">{{cite web | url=http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=602&united=Roy_Smith| title=Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics&nbsp;— Roy Smith | publisher=www.westhamstats.info | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> is an English former [[association football|soccer]] player who played as an [[outside right]] for [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]], [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]].

==Footballing career==
Born in [[Rawalpindi]], [[British Raj|British India]], to English parents, Smith played for [[South Woodford|Woodford]] youth team after his parents returned to the UK. As an [[amateur]] footballer he played for Hereford United before signing professionally for West Ham in 1955 and making his debut against [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on 2 April 1956. Smith played only nine times in his West Ham career in all competitions, scoring one goal. At the end of the [[1956-57 West Ham United F.C. season|1956-57 season]] his contract was not renewed by West Ham and he emigrated with his parents. He returned to the UK in the early 1960s, signing for Portsmouth in 1962.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.11v11.com/players/roy-smith-30967/ | title=Roy Smith | publisher=www.11v11.com | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=Who's Who of West Ham United | publisher=Independent UK Sports Publications | author=Hogg, Tony | year=1995 | location=London | pages=193 | isbn=1-899429-01-8}}</ref>

